# Brace style

Omit curly braces when a control-flow body is a single statement. Prefer putting the statement on the same line as the condition when it fits.

```typescript
// Good
if (!token) return false;
if (!configured) return path.join(projectRoot, 'generated');
if (err.code === 'EBADCSRFTOKEN') return res.status(403).json({ error: 'Invalid CSRF token' });

// Bad — unnecessary braces
if (!token) {
  return false;
}
```

Keep braces when the body has multiple statements or spans multiple lines:

```typescript
if (!secret) {
  secret = tokens.secretSync();
  writeSecret(req, res, secret);
}
```

Applies to `if`, `else`, `for`, `while`, and `do`.
